news.title: Won't conduct structural audits of five high-rises, says IIT-Roorkee
news.para: In February, the department of town and country planning wrote to the premier engineering institute for conducting an audit of the structural strength of the projects — Raheja Vedanta in Sector 108, Raheja Atharva in Sector 109, Brisk Lumbini in Sector 109, M3M Woodshire in Sector 107 and Mahindra Aurai in Sector 110A — in the wake of the Chintels Paradiso housing society tragedy.

news.title: Steel companies withholding rates, supply also not enough: Builders
news.para: ​Procuring steel has also become difficult. This is expected to have a major impact on the infrastructure sector as it uses the equipment. Shortage of construction equipment can slow down infrastructure work, he said.

news.title: Holcim Group considers sale of Indian arms Ambuja Cement, ACC
news.para: Holcim is believed to have held early-stage negotiations with JSW and Adani Group, among others, to explore their interest levels. Both are recent entrants in the cement sector but have aggressive plans to ramp up.

news.title: Only 917 of 9,700 illegal constructions demolished in Nagpur, HC told
news.para: The affidavit was submitted in PILs by Ajay Tiwari through counsel M Anil Kumar contending that the respondents granted approval for construction of houses but failed to act against them for carrying out illegal constructions and non-sanctioned alterations like misusing basement space reserved for parking for another purpose.

news.title: Malls plan rent hikes hearing cash counters ring at stores
news.para: Several retailers saved nearly 20% of their annual lease during the last two years due to rent concessions, which helped curtail net losses. However, over the past few months, retail sales have outpaced the pre-Covid levels, triggering a fresh round of negotiations, companies said.

news.title: Draw of lots for DDA Special Housing Scheme 2021 on April 18
news.para: "Delhi Development Authority is going to conduct a draw for allotment of flats under DDA Special Housing Scheme 2021 on April 18 from 3 PM onwards. It will be based on random number generation system and will be held in the presence of judges, and senior officers of the DDA," a senior official said.

news.title: Rajasthan: 300 developers seek extra time to complete projects
news.para: Over 300 promoters, who failed to meet the self-set deadlines for various reasons including price rise, have sought an extension.

news.title: Telangana: GO 111 beneficiaries elated, but bat for checks on realty
news.para: ​But even they agree that construction activity across the 84 villages, in the future, must be controlled. Some of them also recommend special rules for this “environmentally sensitive belt” so that the reservoirs – Himayatsagar and Osmansagar – remain unaffected.

news.title: Gandhinagar: Residential realty picks up pace at GIFT City
news.para: According to GIFT City officials, some 55 lakh square feet residential real estate space is coming up in the campus with an investment of Rs 2,700 crore over the next five years.

news.title: Over 3.36 lakh families in Kerala own land but have no houses
news.para: This number is likely to vary as the reverification of applications is underway to publish the final list by April 30. Government had received as many as 9,20,260 applications for houses under Life Mission since July 1, 2020.

news.title: Gurugram: Handover of colonies by May 31, DLF wants upkeep fees cleared
news.para: The decision to extend the takeover deadline was taken at a meeting on Wednesday, which was chaired by MCG commissioner Mukesh Kumar Ahuja and attended by DLF representatives.

news.title: Rustomjee Group to set up realty investment platform, raise over Rs 570 crore
news.para: The proposed investment and development platform will focus on real estate projects in Mumbai Metropolitan Region (MMR) mainly in residential and mixed-use developments. Going forward, the platform will also invest in completed mixed-use commercial assets across key cities of the country.

news.title: Government to form committee to study, offer resolutions to stalled housing projects
news.para: The committee will provide a resolution and propose a future course of action to ensure that homebuyers get delivery of their homes in these stalled projects, the Ministry of Housing & Urban Affairs (MoHUA) said.

news.title: Rs 702 crore MahaRERA recovery warrants yet to be executed in Maharashtra
news.para: Latest statistics available with the Maharashtra Real Estate Regulatory Authority (MahaRERA) revealed that such warrants have been issued to developers of 271 projects across the state. Of these, 83 are in Pune, followed by 66 in Mumbai suburban and 50 in Thane.

news.title: Non-execution of 2,600 MahaRERA orders in four years miffs buyers in Maharashtra
news.para: Some of the customers said in cases where the Maharashtra Real Estate Regulatory Authority (MahaRERA) had issued orders in their favour, they had to repeatedly follow up with the developers and ultimately file the non-compliance applications.
